charpov.grader

Annotation Type Test


  • @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
@Target(value=METHOD)
public @interface Test
    Test annotation. This is the only annotation used in the system. In addition to this annotation, a non-static, void, no-argument method named "BEFORE" will be run before each test; similarly, "AFTER" will be run after each test.
    Version:
    1.0, 01/22/12
    Author:
    Michel Charpentier

    • Optional Element Summary

      Optional Elements 
      Modifier and Type Optional Element and Description
      long timeout
      Maximum time allowed to run the test, in milliseconds.
      double val
      The value of this test.

    • Element Detail

      • timeout

        public abstract long timeout
        Maximum time allowed to run the test, in milliseconds. Tests with a timeout of 0 are not given a time limit. Tests with negative values are ignored. If a test does not complete within the allotted time, a TimeoutException is thrown as failure cause.
        See Also:
        TimeoutException
        Default:
        1000L

      • val

        public abstract double val
        The value of this test. Tests with negative values are silently ignored.
        Default:
        0.0
